---
import SciencePin from "~/components/react/SciencePin.tsx";
---

<section id="science" class="border-b border-line bg-ink2/40 relative">
  <SciencePin client:visible />
  <div class="max-w-[1320px] mx-auto px-6 lg:px-10 py-24 lg:py-36">
    <div class="grid lg:grid-cols-12 gap-10 mb-14 lg:mb-20">
      <div class="lg:col-span-3">
        <div class="label mb-3">§ 04 — The science</div>
      </div>
      <div class="lg:col-span-9">
        <h2
          class="display-md text-[clamp(34px,5vw,68px)] font-medium max-w-[22ch] text-paper"
        >
          A transducer, made specific.
        </h2>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="grid lg:grid-cols-12 gap-10 lg:gap-14 items-start">
      <figure class="lg:col-span-6" data-science-figure>
        <div class="border border-line bg-ink p-6 lg:p-8">
          <svg
            viewBox="0 0 480 360"
            class="w-full h-auto"
            role="img"
            aria-label="gFET cross-section schematic"
          >
            <g stroke="#1F1F22" stroke-width="0.5" stroke-dasharray="1 4">
              <line x1="0" y1="80" x2="480" y2="80"></line>
              <line x1="0" y1="180" x2="480" y2="180"></line>
              <line x1="0" y1="280" x2="480" y2="280"></line>
            </g>
            <g stroke="#2A2A2E" stroke-width="1">
              <path d="M10 10 L10 22 M10 10 L22 10"></path>
              <path d="M470 10 L470 22 M470 10 L458 10"></path>
              <path d="M10 350 L10 338 M10 350 L22 350"></path>
              <path d="M470 350 L470 338 M470 350 L458 350"></path>
            </g>
            <rect
              x="40"
              y="270"
              width="400"
              height="50"
              fill="#15151a"
              stroke="#2A2A2E"></rect>
            <text
              x="240"
              y="299"
              text-anchor="middle"
              font-family="JetBrains Mono"
              font-size="11"
              fill="#9A9AA1">Si substrate</text
            >
            <rect
              x="40"
              y="240"
              width="400"
              height="30"
              fill="#1A1A1F"
              stroke="#2A2A2E"></rect>
            <text
              x="240"
              y="259"
              text-anchor="middle"
              font-family="JetBrains Mono"
              font-size="10"
              fill="#9A9AA1">SiO₂ dielectric</text
            >
            <rect
              x="60"
              y="210"
              width="80"
              height="30"
              fill="#2A2A2E"
              stroke="#EDEDE8"></rect>
            <rect
              x="340"
              y="210"
              width="80"
              height="30"
              fill="#2A2A2E"
              stroke="#EDEDE8"></rect>
            <text
              x="100"
              y="230"
              text-anchor="middle"
              font-family="JetBrains Mono"
              font-size="11"
              fill="#EDEDE8">SOURCE</text
            >
            <text
              x="380"
              y="230"
              text-anchor="middle"
              font-family="JetBrains Mono"
              font-size="11"
              fill="#EDEDE8">DRAIN</text
            >
            <line x1="140" y1="210" x2="340" y2="210" stroke="#06B6A7"
              stroke-width="2"></line>
            <text
              x="240"
              y="130"
              text-anchor="middle"
              font-family="JetBrains Mono"
              font-size="10"
              fill="#06B6A7">graphene monolayer</text
            >
            <g class="receptor-flash" stroke="#EDEDE8" stroke-width="1.2"
              fill="none">
              <path d="M170 210 L170 180 M170 180 L160 168 M170 180 L180 168"
              ></path>
              <path d="M210 210 L210 180 M210 180 L200 168 M210 180 L220 168"
              ></path>
              <path d="M250 210 L250 180 M250 180 L240 168 M250 180 L260 168"
              ></path>
              <path d="M290 210 L290 180 M290 180 L280 168 M290 180 L300 168"
              ></path>
              <path d="M330 210 L330 180 M330 180 L320 168 M330 180 L340 168"
              ></path>
            </g>
            <circle class="bound-pulse" cx="210" cy="160" r="5" fill="#06B6A7"
            ></circle>
            <circle class="bound-pulse-2" cx="290" cy="158" r="5" fill="#06B6A7"
            ></circle>
            <circle class="incoming" cx="170" cy="160" r="4" fill="#06B6A7"
              opacity="0.9"></circle>
            <circle class="incoming-2" cx="330" cy="160" r="4" fill="#06B6A7"
              opacity="0.9"></circle>
            <g fill="#06B6A7">
              <circle class="electron" cx="140" cy="210" r="2"></circle>
              <circle class="electron electron-2" cx="140" cy="210" r="2"
              ></circle>
              <circle class="electron electron-3" cx="140" cy="210" r="2"
              ></circle>
            </g>
            <rect
              class="sci-scan"
              x="60"
              y="190"
              width="2"
              height="30"
              fill="#06B6A7"
              opacity="0.85"></rect>
            <text
              x="460"
              y="145"
              text-anchor="end"
              font-family="JetBrains Mono"
              font-size="10"
              fill="#9A9AA1">receptor + bound analyte</text
            >
            <line x1="40" y1="310" x2="20" y2="310" stroke="#EDEDE8"></line>
            <line x1="20" y1="310" x2="20" y2="340" stroke="#EDEDE8"></line>
            <text x="14" y="354" font-family="JetBrains Mono" font-size="10"
              fill="#9A9AA1">V_g</text
            >
            <line x1="60" y1="100" x2="420" y2="100" stroke="#06B6A7"
              stroke-dasharray="2 4" stroke-width="0.8"></line>
            <text x="60" y="92" font-family="JetBrains Mono" font-size="10"
              fill="#06B6A7">electrolyte interface</text
            >
            <text x="20" y="40" font-family="JetBrains Mono" font-size="10"
              fill="#EDEDE8">FIG. A · gFET cross-section</text
            >
            <text
              x="460"
              y="40"
              text-anchor="end"
              font-family="JetBrains Mono"
              font-size="10"
              fill="#6B6B72">scale: schematic</text
            >
          </svg>
          <div class="mt-4 h-px bg-line relative overflow-hidden">
            <div
              data-science-progress
              class="absolute inset-y-0 left-0 bg-accent w-0"
            >
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
        <figcaption class="mt-4 font-mono text-[11px] text-mute">
          FIG. A · Source–graphene–drain channel with receptor-functionalized
          surface. Gate bias V<sub>g</sub> sweeps the Dirac point; analyte
          binding shifts I<sub>ds</sub>(V<sub>g</sub>).
        </figcaption>
      </figure>

      <div class="lg:col-span-6 grid gap-8">
        <div data-science-block>
          <h3
            class="font-mono text-[12px] tracking-[.18em] text-accent uppercase mb-2"
          >
            01 · Graphene as transducer
          </h3>
          <p class="text-paper/85 leading-[1.65] text-[16px]">
            Graphene is one atom thick. Every electron sits at the surface,
            which makes the channel unusually sensitive to whatever lands on
            it. There's no bulk to drown out the signal, so even a single
            binding event shows up as a measurable change in conductance.
          </p>
        </div>
        <div data-science-block>
          <h3
            class="font-mono text-[12px] tracking-[.18em] text-accent uppercase mb-2"
          >
            02 · Surface functionalization
          </h3>
          <p class="text-paper/85 leading-[1.65] text-[16px]">
            The receptors are what make the chip pick out one thing and ignore
            the rest. We covalently bond antibodies, aptamers, or engineered
            binders to the graphene with a linker chemistry that holds up in
            real food matrices. Want to detect something else? Swap the
            receptor.
          </p>
        </div>
        <div data-science-block>
          <h3
            class="font-mono text-[12px] tracking-[.18em] text-accent uppercase mb-2"
          >
            03 · Patented manufacturing
          </h3>
          <p class="text-paper/85 leading-[1.65] text-[16px]">
            We've developed a low-cost way to make lab-grade gFETs at volume —
            cheap enough to ship as a single-use cartridge. That's what lets
            the device sit next to the production line instead of inside a
            research lab.
          </p>
        </div>
        <div data-science-block>
          <h3
            class="font-mono text-[12px] tracking-[.18em] text-accent uppercase mb-2"
          >
            04 · Adaptable across analytes
          </h3>
          <p class="text-paper/85 leading-[1.65] text-[16px]">
            The same platform can answer different questions. Bacteria now,
            viruses next, mycotoxins after that. Re-functionalize the
            surface, re-validate, deploy.
          </p>
        </div>

        <blockquote class="mt-4 border-l-2 border-accent pl-6 py-2">
          <p
            class="text-[20px] lg:text-[22px] leading-[1.4] text-paper tracking-tighter2"
          >
            "Thirty years of graphene research at Chalmers, in a device that
            fits in your hand."
          </p>
          <footer class="mt-3 font-mono text-[11px] text-mute">
            — Research lineage · Chalmers University of Technology
          </footer>
        </blockquote>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>
